context.text: Manchester derby - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
This term is also used in reference to when supporters' offshoot clubs ( Maine Road F.C. and F.C. United of Manchester ) meet.

A large number of non-competitive Manchester derbies have taken place. The majority of these occurred during World War II, when a total of 44 matches were played between the teams. In recent years, non-competitive matches between the teams have generally been testimonials , such as those for Paul Lake and Denis Irwin . Matches between non-first team sides representing the Manchester clubs also have an element of rivalry, with occasions when the reserve teams meet sometimes referred to as "mini-derbies".
all statistics exclude the abandoned match from the 1960/61 season
